on 7/17/03 01:28, Terry K related:
Sodium, or Titanium valves aren't necessarily goig to make the valves
run any cooler---
the sodium is inside the valve. this is completely different than making
the valve from a different alloy. basically the valve is cored out and
filled with salt. the salt (sodium) does not retain heat as much as
solid metal would. that is theory, anyhow.
